subawardee_business_types: PRIVATE UNIVERSITY OR COLLEGE,NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION
subaward_description:
DR. HUS LAB WILL CHARACTERIZE THE PERFORMANCE OF THESE META-LENSES. THIS WILL INVOLVE MEASUREMENTS OF
FOCAL LENGTH, SPOT SIZE, STREHL RATIO, AND FOCUS EFFICIENCY FOR A VARIETY OF WAVELENGTHS IN THE DESIGN
BANDWIDTH. THEY WILL ALSO INVESTIGATE IMAGING PERFORMANCE OVER THE DESIGN BANDWIDTH VIA TEST IMAGES
INCLUDING STANDARD AIR FORCE RESOLUTION CHARTS.
THE MIT TEAM WILL FABRICATE AND CHARACTERIZE A SET OF META-SURFACES TO VALIDATE THE DESIGNS. SPECIFICALLY,
THREE SETS OF SAMPLES WILL BE FABRICATED AND CONTRASTED: 1) META-SURFACES COMPRISING META-ATOMS OF
REGULAR GEOMETRIES (CIRCLES, SQUARES, AND RECTANGLES); 2) META-SURFACES COMPRISING FREE-FORM METAATOMS;
AND 3) META-SURFACES CONTAINING THE SAME SETS OF DESIGNS AS 1) AND 2) BUT WITH INTENTIONALLY
INTRODUCED, CONTROLLED VARIATIONS (E.G. SIZE VARIATIONS, CORNER ROUNDING, DISTORTIONS, NON-VERTICAL
SIDEWALLS, ETC.) TO INVESTIGATE DESIGN ROBUSTNESS AGAINST GEOMETRY DEVIATIONS. THE SAMPLES WILL BE
FABRICATED OUT OF SI-ON-GLASS, A COMMONLY ADOPTED META-SURFACE PLATFORM SUCH THAT NOT ONLY THE DESIGN
APPROACH CAN BE VALIDATED, BUT ALSO THE EXPERIMENTAL RESULTS WILL BE BROADLY USEFUL TO THE META-SURFACE
COMMUNITY. THE MIT GROUP HAVE ALREADY ESTABLISHED MATURE PROCESSES FOR SI-ON-GLASS META-SURFACE
FABRICATION, WHICH INVOLVES ELECTRON BEAM LITHOGRAPHY PATTERNING AND PLASMA ETCHING [YAN]. WE CHOOSE
ELECTRON BEAM LITHOGRAPHY HERE SINCE ITS FINE RESOLUTION ALLOWS US TO RELIABLY SIMULATE VARIOUS GEOMETRY
DEVIATIONS.
EACH SET OF SAMPLES WILL BE CHARACTERIZED USING A STANDARD SET OF MEASUREMENTS TO QUANTITATIVELY ASSESS
THEIR PERFORMANCES. ONCE THE SAMPLES ARE PROCESSED, WE WILL USE HIGH-RESOLUTION SCANNING ELECTRON
MICROSCOPY (SEM) TO EXAMINE THE PATTERN FIDELITY. THE MIT GROUP HAVE DEVELOPED AN AUTOMATIC IMAGE
PROCESSING PACKAGE WHICH EXTRACTS THE DIMENSIONS OF FABRICATED META-ATOMS FROM SEM IMAGES TO
FACILITATE HIGH-THROUGHPUT CHARACTERIZATION OF META- OPTICAL DEVICES.
OPTICAL TESTING OF THE META-LENSES CONSISTS OF 1) BULK TRANSMISSION EFFICIENCY MEASUREMENT, WHICH CAN BE
STRAIGHTFORWARDLY OBTAINED BY PLACING A LARGE-AREA DETECTOR BEHIND THE LENS TO CAPTURE ALL TRANSMITTED
POWER; 2) FOCAL SPOT CHARACTERIZATIONS, INCLUDING FOCUSING EFFICIENCY AND STREHL RATIO; AND 3) IMAGING
TESTS.
THE MIT TEAM HAVE SUCCESSFULLY IMPLEMENTED THE MEASUREMENT PROTOCOLS ON VARIOUS META-LENS DESIGNS,
AND SOME EXAMPLES INCLUDE DEMONSTRATION OF THE FIRST MID-IR META-LENS WITH SUB-WAVELENGTH IMAGING
CAPABILITY [ZHA], A FLAT FISHEYE LENS WITH NEAR--OF-VIEW [SHA1], A VARIFOCAL METALENS WITH
DIFFRACTION-LIMITED QUALITY [SHA2], AND A PARFOCAL ZOOM META-LENS WITHOUT MECHANICAL MOVING PARTS.
[ZHA] WE NOTE THAT HIGH OPTICAL PERFORMANCES IN THESE DEVICES WERE WARRANTED ONLY THROUGH PROPERLY
ACCOUNTING FOR FABRICATION NON-IDEALITIES IN THE META-SURFACE DESIGN [SHA3]. THE SAME SYNERGISTIC DESIGN
AND FABRICATION CONSIDERATIONS WILL BE LEVERAGED IN THE PROPOSED STUDY.
2.0.1 PROTOTYPE T&E VALIDATION EFFORTS
BUILD AND TEST 5-10 META-LENS PROTOTYPES: WE WILL WORK WITH DR. HUS LAB AT MIT TO SPECIFY A MATRIX OF
LENSES FOR LITHOGRAPHY BASED ON DESIGNS FOR AF END USER PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS. HE WILL HELP IDENTIFY
APPROPRIATE NANO- LITHOGRAPHY MANUFACTURING PROCESSES AND NORMAL AND FORCED VARIABILITY THEREOF. HE
WILL FABRICATE 5-10 META-LENSES THAT WILL VARY IN TERMS OF DESIGN THAT VARY IN META-CELL SHAPE AND DESIGN
WAVELENGTH, BANDWIDTH, AND FOCAL LENGTH. FIVE OF THESE DESIGNS WILL EXPLORE MANUFACTURING VARIABILITY
11
WITH META-CELLS RANGE, BOTH SMALLER AND LARGER. DR. HUS LAB WILL CHARACTERIZE THE PERFORMANCE OF LENSES,
MEASURING FOCAL LENGTH, SPOT SIZE, STREHL RATIO, AND FOCUS EFFICIENCY FOR A VARIETY OF WAVELENGTHS IN THE
DESIGN BANDWIDTH. WE WILL ALSO INVESTIGATE IMAGING PERFORMANCE OVER THE DESIGN BANDWIDTH VIA TEST
IMAGES, INCLUDING WIDELY USED AIR FORCE STANDARD RESOLUTION CHARTS.

subaward_description:
EXPANSION OF THE VIRTUAL TEXTILE MORPHOLOGY SOFTWARE (VTMS) TO SIMULATE MANUFACTURING PROCESSES.
VTMS HAS BEEN DEVELOPED AND USED TO RECREATE REALISTIC TEXTILE CROSS-SECTIONS; THERE HAS BEEN LESS FOCUS
ON MECHANICALLY REPRODUCING LOADS IN A MANUFACTURING SIMULATION OF THE COMPACTION PROCESS.

THIS WORK WILL ATTEMPT TO REPLICATE THE COMPACTION PROCESS OF A WOVEN TEXTILE USING VTMS. THE
INTRODUCTION OF FIBER ENTANGLEMENT WITHIN EACH TOW WILL BE USED TO REPRODUCE REALISTIC TRANSVERSE BEHAVIOR
OF THE TOWS. FINALLY, INPUT PARAMETERS NEEDED TO REPRODUCE EXPERIMENTAL PRESSURE RESPONSE WILL BE
DETERMINED.

subaward_description: SUPPLIER WILL PROVIDE CLIENT WITH ENGINEERING PERSONNEL TO SUPPORT THE USAF CLOUD ONE PROGRAM FOR THE PURPOSES OF, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, ARCHITECUTURAL ANALYSIS CONSULTATION, CLOUD-COMPUTING DESIGN AND IMPLEMENTATION, AND SOLUTION MIGRATION OF USAF APPLICATION FROM ON-PREMISE DATA CENTERS TO GOVERNMENT CLOUD ENVIRONMENTS PROVIDED BY THE CLOUD ONE PROGRAM (I.E. AMAZON WEB SERVICES, MICROSOFT AZURE, ORACLE CLOUD INFRASTRUCTURE, GOOGLE CLOUD PLATFORM). ENGINEERING PERSONNEL WILL BE ASSIGNED TEAMS AND TASKED BY CLIENT PROGRAM MANAGERS AND TECHNICAL LEADS AS A PART OF THE OVERALL GROUP OF CLOUD ONE MIGRATION, CYBER, O&S, OR DATA TRANSPORT TEAMS. WHILE TRAVEL IS EXPECTED TO BE LIMITED, TACTWARE WILL PROVIDE ON-SITE SUPPORT FOR CLIENT AND USAF NEED TASKED BY CLIENT PROGRAM MANAGERS AND TECHNICAL LEADS AS A PART OF THE OVERALL GROUP OF CLOUD ONE MIGRATION, CYBER, O&S, OR DATA TRANSPORT TEAMS. WHILE TRAVEL IS EXPECTED TO BE LIMITED, TACTWARE WILL PROVIDE ON-SITE SUPPORT FOR CLIENT AND USAF NEED TASKED BY CLIENT PROGRAM MANAGERS AND TECHNICAL LEADS AS A PART OF THE OVERALL GROUP OF CLOUD ONE MIGRATION, CYBER, O&S, OR DATA TRANSPORT TEAMS. WHILE TRAVEL IS EXPECTED TO BE LIMITED, TACTWARE WILL PROVIDE ON-SITE SUPPORT FOR CLIENT AND USAF NEEDS IN SUPPORT OF THE CLOUD ONE PROGRAM.

subaward_description: SUPPLIER WILL PROVIDE CLIENT WITH ENGINEERING PERSONNEL TO SUPPORT THE USAF CLOUD ONE PROGRAM FOR THE PURPOSES OF, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, ARCHITECUTURAL ANALYSIS CONSULTATION, CLOUD-COMPUTING DESIGN AND IMPLEMENTATION, AND SOLUTION MIGRATION OF USAF APPLICATION FROM ON-PREMISE DATA CENTERS TO GOVERNMENT CLOUD ENVIRONMENTS PROVIDED BY THE CLOUD ONE PROGRAM (I.E. AMAZON WEB SERVICES, MICROSOFT AZURE, ORACLE CLOUD INFRASTRUCTURE, GOOGLE CLOUD PLATFORM). ENGINEERING PERSONNEL WILL BE ASSIGNED TEAMS AND TASKED BY CLIENT PROGRAM MANAGERS AND TECHNICAL LEADS AS A PART OF THE OVERALL GROUP OF CLOUD ONE MIGRATION, CYBER, O&S, OR DATA TRANSPORT TEAMS. WHILE TRAVEL IS EXPECTED TO BE LIMITED, TACTWARE WILL PROVIDE ON-SITE SUPPORT FOR CLIENT AND USAF NEED TASKED BY CLIENT PROGRAM MANAGERS AND TECHNICAL LEADS AS A PART OF THE OVERALL GROUP OF CLOUD ONE MIGRATION, CYBER, O&S, OR DATA TRANSPORT TEAMS. WHILE TRAVEL IS EXPECTED TO BE LIMITED, TACTWARE WILL PROVIDE ON-SITE SUPPORT FOR CLIENT AND USAF NEEDS IN SUPPORT OF THE CLOUD ONE PROGRAM.

subaward_description: THE INTENT OF THIS PROJECT IS TO PROVIDE FOR THE REPAIR AND SUSTAINMENT OF CENTRAL PLANT, BUILDING 1201 (B1201), TO INCLUDE REPLACEMENT OF A BOILER, REPLACEMENT OF ELECTRIC CHILLER #2 WITH AN ABSORPTION CHILLER, REPAIR, REPLACEMENT, AND MODERNIZATION OF MECHANICAL AND ELECTRICAL INFRASTRUCTURE, CONTROLS, AND EQUIPMENT; REPAIRS AND UPGRADES TO PLANT ARCHITECTURAL ELEMENTS, NEW CATWALKS, ABATEMENT OF HAZARDOUS MATERIALS, REPAIRS TO EXISTING METAL STACKS, REPLACEMENT OF THE EXISTING GENERATOR, INSTALLATION OF A NEW UNINTERRUPTIBLE POWER SUPPLY (UPS) PANEL, CONVERSION OF THE CENTRAL PLANT TO USE #2 FUEL OIL, UPGRADES TO COOLING TOWER HYDRAULICS, IMPROVEMENTS TO PLANT PIPING SYSTEMS, AS WELL AS OTHER REPAIRS, UPGRADES, AND SAFETY IMPROVEMENTS.

subawardee_business_types: PRIVATE UNIVERSITY OR COLLEGE,NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION
subaward_description:
THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS PROGRAM IS FOR THE PI NIAN SUN TO WORK CLOSELY WITH PROF. TAYLOR H. WARE FROM TAMU, DR. CEDRIC AMBULO WITH ELECTRONINKS AND DR. MICHAEL MCCONNEY FROM WPAFB ON DESIGNING PROGRAMMABLE PRINTED CIRCUIT BOARDS (PPCBS). NIAN WILL WORK WITH AFRL TO IDENTIFY DEVICES AND/OR APPLICATION TO DESIGN CIRCUITS FOR, SUCH AS ANTENNA.  THE FOLLOWING TASKS ARE PLANNED:

1. NIAN WILL DEVELOP A RELATIVELY SIMPLE MODELING SOFTWARE ROUTINE TO ACCOUNT FOR THE LIQUID CRYSTAL ANISOTROPIC DIELECTRIC CONSTANT.  
2. NIAN WILL DESIGN HIGH FREQUENCY TRANSMISSION LINES, ANTENNA AND EXAMINE CHIP INTERCONNECT STRUCTURES TO LOOK FOR UNIQUE ASPECTS TO APPLY THIS TECHNOLOGY
3. IDENTIFY NEW APPLICATIONS THAT CAN TAKE ADVANTAGE OF PPCBS FROM PROF. WARES LABORATORY, INCLUDING RECONFIGURABLE TRANSMISSION LINES, RECONFIGURABLE FILTERS, AND RECONFIGURABLE ANTENNAS.
4. DESIGN AND SIMULATION OF RECONFIGURABLE ELECTRONICS WITH PPCBS.
5. FABRICATION AND TESTING OF RECONFIGURABLE ELECTRONICS WITH PPCBS.
6. IDENTIFICATION OF THE BENEFITS OF RECONFIGURABLE ELECTRONICS WITH PPCBS, RANGING FROM RECONFIGURABILITY, TUNABILITY, BROADBAND, NEW FUNCTIONALITY, ETC.

prime_award_program_activities_funding_t: 0030: N/A;0099: N/A;009S: MISCELLANEOUS
prime_award_base_transaction_description: POLYMERS AND RESPONSIVE MATERIALS R&D AND EXPLORATION
prime_award_naics_description: RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT IN THE PHYSICAL, ENGINEERING, AND LIFE SCIENCES (EXCEPT NANOTECHNOLOGY AND BIOTECHNOLOGY)
subawardee_business_types: PRIVATE UNIVERSITY OR COLLEGE,NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION
subaward_description:
1.0 OBJECTIVE
THE BELOW OBJECTIVES SHOULD BE PERFORMED ON REACTORS THAT ARE SUITED FOR (OR MIMIC) ON-ORBIT CHEMICAL
MANUFACTURING. IDEALLY, THESE REACTIONS SHOULD BE PERFORMED IN PROTOTYPES TO FACILITATE ALIGNMENT WITH AXIOM
SPACE. THIS WILL ENSURE THAT ANY REACTIONS, REACTORS AND CHEMISTRY PERFORMED WILL BE AMENABLE TO ON-ORBIT
CHEMISTRY SHOULD THE OPPORTUNITY PRESENT ITSELF. THE BROAD OBJECTIVES LISTED BELOW ARE MEANT TO BE MOTIVATION
RATHER THAN PRESCRIPTIVE ON THE WORK TO BE PERFORMED.
1.1 OBJECTIVE 1
DEMONSTRATE AND EXPLORE NEW MATERIALS SYNTHESIS USING CONTINUOUS FLOW. TARGET OBJECTIVES SHOULD INCLUDE
DEMONSTRATIONS OF LINEAR HYDROCARBON POLYMERS AND/OR POLYMER GRAFTED NANOPARTICLE BLENDS THAT HAVE BROAD
AIR FORCE APPLICABILITY FOR COMPOSITES, SOFT ROBOTICS, AND ELECTRONICS.
1.2 OBJECTIVE 2
INCORPORATE AUTOMATION, MACHINE LEARNING, AND/OR SOFTWARE INTO THE CURRENT FLOW SYSTEM. IDEALLY, THE PROPOSER
SHOULD BE ABLE TO ADD AUTOMATION/DATA COLLECTION AND ITERATIVE EXPERIMENTATION.
1.3 OBJECTIVE 3
MATURE THE FLOW CHEMISTRY AND/OR REACTOR DESIGN FOR POLYMER SYNTHESIS AND POLYMER GRAFTED NANOPARTICLE
CRYSTALLIZATION. EXPLORE NEW REACTOR GEOMETRIES, CAPABILITIES SUCH AS FILM DEPOSITION, PHOTOCHEMICAL,
HEAT/COOLED, LIQUID/LIQUID SEPARATION, FILTRATION, SOLVENT EXCHANGE ETC. DEVELOP A PARTS LIST, MANUAL FOR PUTTING
THE SYSTEM TOGETHER AND STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURE ON THE FLOW CHEMISTRY REACTOR.
